The paper deals with the problem of dense light field reconstruction, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed approach involves a learning-based framework (cs.MM) and a novel network architecture (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of transfer learning (cs.LG) to achieve non-Lambertian performance.
